observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct:

The Municipal Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Officer-Designate to prepare and submit LDRRMFIP and budget in accordance with the prescribed format;
The Municipal Budget Officer to maintain Registries of Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations for each of the QRF, MOOE & CO.
The Municipal Accountant to regularly prepare the monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRM Fund and submit to the Audit Team;

Further, the Municipal Accountant should determine the unexpended balances for QRF & MOOE and transfer the same to a special trust fund to be used solely for the purpose of supporting disaster risk reduction and management activities of the Municipality within the next five years.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
Spearhead the immediate liquidation of the cash advances granted to LGU officials/employees. 
Introduce controls that would assure that cash advances are liquidated or reported as soon as the purpose of the cash advance is served;
Refrain from granting additional cash advances to officers and employees with unsettled cash advances to avoid the accumulation of unliquidated cash advances; 
Request write-off of long outstanding/dormant cash advances and attached therein complete documents as enumerated in COA Circular 2016-005;
Cause the withholding of salaries or any money due the officers and employees with overdue unliquidated cash advances to compel its settlement; and
f. File appropriate charges against persons liable if warranted, for continuous failure to settle their accountabilities upon demand.

